/SCC/XXOMMENTARY./XX The blessing immediately following the
Shema deals with the theme of divine redemption. The present text, a
rewritten version, includes references to the Holocaust, from which there
was no redemption, and the return to Zion, a fulfillment of Israelòs ancient
dream. The same divine spirit that gave Israel the courage to seek freedom
from Egypt in ancient times inspired those who fought for Israelòs freedom
in our own day. At the same time, this version omits those portions of the
text that glory in the enemyòs fall or see in God a force for vengeance.
All humans are Godòs beloved children, as were the Egyptians who
drowned at the sea./PR

/SC/XXA.G./XX/PR

/PR

/PR

/PR

