/KAVESHAMERU / OBSERVING SHABBAT/XX/PR

Let Israelòs descendants keep Shabbat, making Shabbat
throughout all their generations, as an eternal bond. Between
me and Israelòs descendants shall it be a sign eternally. For in six
days /SCT/XXHE /XXF/XXASHIONER /XXO/XXF /XXA/XXLL/XX made skies and earth, and on the
seventh day God ceased and drew a breath of rest./PR

/IT(When Shabbat coincides with a festival, add:/PR

/PR

Moses proclaimed the Festivals of /SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXNDURING /XXO/XXNE/XX to the
children of Israel.)/PR

/SCN/XXOTE/XX. The placement of /ITVeshameru/XX after /ITHashkivenu/XX suggests an aspect of
the agreement between God and Israel: God guards Israel, and Israel
guards Shabbat, which is a reminder and foretaste of peace in our world./PR

/SC/XXS.S./XX/PR

/PR

/SCK/XXAVANAH/XX. The recitations of /ITVeshameru/XX preceding the /ITAmidah/XX and of
/ITVayh/±ulu/XX following it on Friday evening are acts of witnessing. In keeping
Shabbat Israel bears testimony to the fact that ours is a created world. For
us this means that divinity fills the universe. Our task is to treat all living
things with respect, and so enhance the divine light in them. Only by this
way of living is the testimony of Shabbat made real.    /SC/XXA.G./XX/PR

/PR

